1 olive oil
1 packet beef mince
1 bag Soffritto Mix
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet tomato paste
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 tin sweetcorn
2 radish
½ lemon
1 bag salad leaves
1 bag herbs
1 packet burger sauce
1 packet sour cream
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef and soffritto mix, breaking up with a spoon, until beef is browned, 2-3 mins
• Stir in garlic paste and spice blend, cook until fragrant, 1 min
• Add tomato paste and a good splash of water
• Stir until heated, 1 min

• Meanwhile, microwave rice until steaming, 2-3 mins
• Drain corn. Trim and thinly slice radish
• Cut lemon into wedges
• In a bowl, combine corn and radish

• To the bowl, add salad leaves, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of oil. Season and toss
• Plate up rice, beef and salad. Top with Cheddar
• Serve with burger sauce, sour cream, torn herbs and remaining lemon wedges